# gRPC and Protobuf Standards

## Proto design rules

```protobuf
// WRONG — no package versioning; breaking changes break all clients
syntax = "proto3";
package auth;

// RIGHT — versioned package, explicit Go package
syntax = "proto3";
package ibex.auth.v1;
option go_package = "github.com/Rick1330/ibex-harness/packages/proto/ibex/auth/v1;authv1";
```

### Field rules
- Fields are `snake_case` in proto, become `CamelCase` in generated Go
- Never reuse a field number once it's been released (mark reserved)
- All UUID fields are `string`, not `bytes` — readability in logs outweighs the tiny size win
- All timestamps are `google.protobuf.Timestamp`, not `int64`
- Add `// (required)` comment for fields that must be set; proto3 has no required keyword

```protobuf
// WRONG — reusing field number 3 for a different field
message Request {
    string org_id   = 1;
    string agent_id = 2;
    // string old_field = 3; // removed
    string new_field = 3; // BUG: reused number — breaks old clients
}

// RIGHT — reserve removed field numbers
message Request {
    string org_id   = 1; // (required) UUID string
    string agent_id = 2; // (required) UUID string
    reserved 3;
    reserved "old_field";
    string new_field = 4;
}
```

## gRPC server — error code discipline

Map every failure mode to the correct gRPC status code. Never invent codes.

| Situation | gRPC Code | HTTP Mapping |
|---|---|---|
| UUID parse failure | `INVALID_ARGUMENT` | 400 |
| Missing required field | `INVALID_ARGUMENT` | 400 |
| Token revoked | `UNAUTHENTICATED` | 401 |
| Token expired | `UNAUTHENTICATED` | 401 |
| Cross-org resource access | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | 403 |
| Agent not active | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | 403 |
| Resource not found (own org) | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 |
| DB/Redis failure | `INTERNAL` (log original) | 503 |
| Deadline exceeded | `DEADLINE_EXCEEDED` | 504 |
| Context cancelled | `CANCELED` | — |

```go
// WRONG — NOT_FOUND leaks resource existence across orgs
return nil, status.Errorf(codes.NotFound, "agent %s not found", agentID)

// RIGHT — PERMISSION_DENIED for all cross-tenant denials
return nil, status.Errorf(codes.PermissionDenied,
    "agent is not authorized for this organization")
```

## gRPC client — always enforce deadline

```go
// WRONG — no deadline; single hung auth service hangs all proxy requests
resp, err := s.authClient.ValidateToken(ctx, req)

// RIGHT — per-call deadline from ARCHITECTURE.md budget
func (c *AuthClient) ValidateToken(ctx context.Context, token string) (*authv1.ValidateTokenResponse, error) {
    const budget = 50 * time.Millisecond
    ctx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, budget)
    defer cancel()
    return c.client.ValidateToken(ctx, connect.NewRequest(&authv1.ValidateTokenRequest{Token: token}))
}
```

## gRPC connection — keepalive and retry

```go
// WRONG — default connection; silently dies after network blip
conn, _ := grpc.Dial(addr)

// RIGHT — keepalive, wait-for-ready, retry policy
conn, err := grpc.NewClient(
    addr,
    grpc.WithTransportCredentials(insecure.NewCredentials()), // mTLS in production
    grpc.WithKeepaliveParams(keepalive.ClientParameters{
        Time:                10 * time.Second, // send keepalive ping every 10s
        Timeout:             5 * time.Second,  // wait 5s for pong
        PermitWithoutStream: true,
    }),
    grpc.WithDefaultServiceConfig(`{
        "methodConfig": [{
            "name": [{}],
            "waitForReady": true,
            "retryPolicy": {
                "maxAttempts": 3,
                "initialBackoff": "0.1s",
                "maxBackoff": "1s",
                "backoffMultiplier": 2,
                "retryableStatusCodes": ["UNAVAILABLE"]
            }
        }]
    }`),
)
```

## Never commit generated proto code

Generated files (`*.pb.go`, `*_grpc.pb.go`, `*connect.go`) are regenerated by `make proto-gen`. They are gitignored. Adding them to the repository creates merge conflicts and false diffs in code review.
